tables.table_title: Expected running time (ERT in number of function evaluations) divided by the best ERT measured during BBOB-2009 (given in the respective first row) for different $\Delta f$ values for functions $f_{1}-f_{24}$. The median number of conducted function evaluations is additionally given in italics, if $\operatorname{ERT}\left(10^{-7}\right)=\infty$. \#succ is the number of trials that reached the final target $f_{\text {opt }}+10^{-8}$. 0: pPO is pPOEMS and 1: Cau is CauchyEDA. Bold entries are statistically significantly better compared to the other algorithm, with $p=0.05$ or $p=10^{-k}$ where $k>1$ is the number following the $*$ symbol, with Bonferroni correction of 48.
